-- MOVES-Arbuthnot Latham & Co appoint private bankers at Exeter office
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 02:38PM EDT
-- None



Sept 11 (Reuters) - Arbuthnot Banking Group Plc's <ARBB.L> private banking and wealth management unit appointed two private bankers at its Exeter office.

Arbuthnot Latham & Co named Chris Reah as senior private banker and Matthew Elliott as private banker, effective immediately. Reah's new role will see him run the banking team at Exeter and act as an investment adviser as well. Ian Scott, who heads the wealth planning division, will now also lead the company's South West regional office, Arbuthnot said. Reah and Elliot have previously worked at Coutts & Co.   (Bangalore newsroom; moves@thomsonreuters.com)  Keywords: ARBUTHNOTLATHAM&CO MOVES/CHRIS REAH